4:
Wow, are your legs seriously bionic
prosthetics? You're so freaking cool!
6:
That takes surgery, right? Sounds
intense...
9:
Yeah, it hurt like crazy, but I'm used
to them now! Next time I'm gonna
get a mod so I can change my toe
nail color!
13:
Tink, mind if I borrow this book? 
I'll have it back here by tomorrow!
16:
Sure thing! Those books have just
been lying around anyway.
20:
Oh! Hey, Yumu! Gotta go! See ya
later!
27:
Come on in, you two! And Happy
New Year, Nimbus!
30:
Right back at you. But... man. You're
making yourself right at home, huh?
33:
Nyahaha! Everyone loves it here.
Plus, I'm having a blast, so it's
probably fine!
36:
Whoa, sick... Cocoa, get a load of
that. That tiger can talk.
38:
No cap? Crazy. No way it's a tiger?
Maybe it's a dude in a fur suit!
40: This "fur suit" can hear you, y'know.
44:
Let me introduce you! These are my
new friends, Cocoa and Mocha!
47:
And guess whaaat? They're gonna
tag along with us today on monster
patrol!
52:
You sure about that? Seems like
they'll do more harm than good...
55:
Hey, don't count us out, Nimbus. 
We have our ways. Besides, 
we shadowed Tink yesterday!
58:
Cocoa and Mocha are looking for a
way to make a little spending
money. And, we've got the budget
for part-timers!
61:
So don't worry about it. I'll take full
responsibility if anything happens,
yada yada. Anyway, now that we're
all here, let's hit the streets!
67:
Nyahaha, thanks a lot for your help,
you two! I feel much better knowing
you have my back!
72:
Hear that, Nimbus? Tink says we're
HELPING. Are you impressed yet?
74:
Sure, sure. Whatever helps you sleep
at night.
79:
Things seem pretty quiet around
here today. Let's finish our sweep of
this area and—
84: Wait... It can't be. Not again!
87:
Niiice! Is this like, a boss fight?! Woo!
Let's do this, Mocha!
89:
Right, Cocoa! That thing doesn't
stand a chance!
94:
Phew... Did that thing crawl out of a
manga or what?
98:
Not quite... That's Benten. I never
thought I'd see her again.
102:
Well, she should stop popping out of
nowhere! The next time it happens,
I'll knock her into next week!
105:
Anyway, let's head back. Looks like
the monsters are done for now.
108:
Yeah, but real talk... I just wanna go
home...
110:
Ugh... We blew it. We're really sorry,
Tink...
113:
All right, you two head directly
home! Thanks for your work today,
ladies!
118: Think they're gonna be all right?
121:
I'm sure they'll be fine. After all,
they've got Tink.
125:
Yaaawn... The toughest boss of all:
the sleepies. I just wanna stay under
the kotatsu forever!
128:
Nyahah! No can do! You're on
tangerine-serving duty!
133:
Hey, Tink... Be honest. Do you think
we should quit?
139:
I mean, we suck. Like, majorly. You
saw what happened today.
140:
Feels like we're just getting in the
way. And what if someone bit the
big one all because of us? Y'know...
game over for real?
143:
Well, it IS a dangerous job, so I
understand if you wanna move on.
147:
Remember, though. Just 'cause you
mess up once doesn't mean it's all
over. People make mistakes.
150:
No matter what happens, I'll always
be on your side. Even if you decide
to quit, you can still come hang out
here anytime! In fact, please do!
153:
And regardless of what path you
choose, I'll never let anything bad
happen to either of you. Period!
156: Ugh. You're SO freaking cool, Tink...
162:
Well, if you put it like that... do you
mind if we keep at it a little longer?
164:
Of course not! Duh! And I'll be
protecting you the whole way!
170:
Whoa, Nova. Your handwriting is on
point. It's not fair you're handsome
AND godlike at everything.
172:
Thanks, Mocha. But I think you're the
cutest.
175:
Could you two NOT? If there's
anything I hate more than pretty
boys who always get their way, 
it's their enablers!
179:
So... Did those two decide to stay on
as part-timers?
182:
They sure did. All it took was a pep
talk from me... plus a little showing
off.
185:
But don't get me wrong, I meant
every word of it!
188:
Hey, Tink! Can we stop by the office
today?
191:
Sure thing! The old-timers should be
holding down the fort, so do me a
favor and play some mahjong with
them!
195:
It sure is getting lively back at the
office.
199:
Nyahaha! I kind of like it! Keeps me
on my toes.
202:
I just wish I could keep the Shibuya
branch open a little longer...
205:
Tink, help a girl out! I seriously need
to get myself some of those bionic
prosthetic thingies for my legs, too!
209:
You bet! I'll hook you up! Who else is
up for a quick trip to Qualia City?
